12/08/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Ministry of Foreign Affairs and European Integration expressed regret on Tuesday (August11th) over an incident last week incident involving Oscar-winning Czech film director Jiri Menzel. 
While working on a documentary called "My Croatia" for the Croatian National Television (HRT) in Dubrovnik, Menzel was attacked a week ago by the owner and employees of a local restaurant. 
The owner was allegedly furious because Menzel's camera had covered the restaurant's signboard on the street. 
The foreign ministry stressed that all foreign travellers are welcome in Croatia and authorities will make sure that each stay is secure. 
After the incident, Czech media urged travellers to avoid Croatia. 
(HINA, Javno, Novi List - 11/08/09)
